'''227''' ('''two hundred [and] twenty-seven''') is the natural number between [[226 (number)|226]] and [[228 (number)|228]]. It is also a [[prime number]].

==In mathematics==
227 is a [[twin prime]] and the start of a [[prime triplet]] (with [[229 (number)|229]] and [[233 (number)|233]]).<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A022004|Initial members of prime triples (p, p+2, p+6)}}</ref> It is a [[safe prime]], as dividing it by two and rounding down produces the [[Sophie Germain prime]] [[113 (number)|113]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A005385|Safe primes}}</ref> It is also a [[regular prime]],<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A007703|name=Regular primes}}</ref> a [[Pillai prime]],<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A063980|name=Pillai primes}}</ref> a [[Stern prime]],<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A042978|Stern primes}}</ref> and a [[Ramanujan prime]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A104272|name=Ramanujan primes}}</ref>

The 227th [[harmonic number]] is the first to exceed six.<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A002387|name=Least k such that H(k) > n, where H(k) is the harmonic number sum_{i=1..k} 1/i}}</ref> There are 227 different [[connected graph]]s with eight edges,<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A002905|Number of connected graphs with n edges}}</ref> and 227 [[independent set (graph theory)|independent sets]] in a 3&nbsp;&times;&nbsp;4 [[grid graph]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A051736|Number of 3 x n (0,1)-matrices with no consecutive 1's in any row or column}}</ref>

