281 is the [[60 (number)|60]]th prime, [[twin prime]] with 283, [[Sophie Germain prime]], sum of the first fourteen primes, sum of seven consecutive primes (29 + 31 + 37 + 41 + 43 + 47 + 53), [[Chen prime]], [[Eisenstein prime]] with no imaginary part, [[centered decagonal number]].

281 is the smallest prime ''p'' such that the [[decimal]] [[period length]] of the [[Multiplicative inverse|reciprocal]] of ''p'' is (''p''−1)/10, i.e. the period length of 1/281 is 28. However, in [[binary number system|binary]], it has period length 70.

The generalized [[repunit]] number <math>\frac{281^p-1}{280}</math> is [[composite number|composite]] for all prime ''p'' < 60000.


