'''511''' is the [[natural number]] following [[510 (number)|510]] and preceding [[512 (number)|512]].

It is a [[Mersenne number]], being one less than a power of 2: <math>511=2^9-1</math>.
As a result, 511 is a palindromic number and a [[repdigit]] in bases 2 (111111111<sub>2</sub>). It is also palindromic and a repdigit in base 8 (777<sub>8</sub>).

It is a generalized [[heptagonal number]] {{OEIS|id=A085787}}, since 
<math>511=\frac{1}{2}(5n^2-3n)</math> when <math>n=-14</math>.

It is a [[Harshad number]] in bases 3, 5, 7, 10, 13 and 15.


== Special use in computers ==
The octal representation of 511 (777<sub>8</sub>) is commonly used by Unix commands to specify a custom record separator in order to "slurp" input as a whole, rather than line-by-line (i.e. separated at [[newline]] characters).

